{"word":"H3960 - לָשַׁן - lâshan - law-shan' - Accuse","slug":"H3960","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לָשַׁן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lâshan"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>law-shan'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Accuse"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05DF; - la&#x0302;shan</b> - <i>law-shan'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>lick</i>; but used only as a denominative from <a href=\"#/H3956\">H3956</a>; to <i>wag the tongue</i>, that is, to <i>calumniate: - </i>accuse, slander."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3956\">H3956</a>, <a href=\"#/H3962\">H3962</a>"}]}